# Button and Icon Styling Rules

This rule is here to keep the buttons within the app pretty standard.

## Inline Delete Icon
When needing a small icon for a delete button:
```html
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 7l-.867 12.142A2 2 0 0116.138 21H7.862a2 2 0 01-1.995-1.858L5 7m5 4v6m4-6v6m1-10V4a1 1 0 00-1-1h-4a1 1 0 00-1 1v3M4 7h16"></path>
</svg>
```

## Large Delete Button - Red
Styling for a large delete button:
```html
<button class="bg-red-500 text-white hover:bg-red-600">Delete</button>
```

## Inline Cancel Icon
When needing a small icon for a cancel button:
```html
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"></path>
</svg>
```
## Large Cancel Button - Red
Styling for a large cancel button:
```html
<button class="bg-grey-300 text-red hover:bg-grey-400 px-4 py-2 rounded">Cancel</button>
```
```html
<a style="background-color: #D1D5DB; color: #ff0000; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; border-radius: 0.25rem; display: inline-block; transition: background-color 0.3s;">Cancel</a>
```

